      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a Python function implementing the Nearest Neighbor heuristic that iterates through the matrix, selects the closest unvisited node at each step, and sums the edge weights to return the total path distance:\n\n```python\ndef nearest_neighbor_vrp(dist_matrix):\n    num_nodes = len(dist_matrix)\n    unvisited = set(range(1, num_nodes))\n    total_distance = 0\n    current = 0\n\n    while unvisited:\n        min_dist = float('inf')\n        next_node = -1\n        for neighbor in unvisited:\n            cost = dist_matrix[current][neighbor]\n            if cost < min_dist:\n                min_dist = cost\n                next_node = neighbor\n        unvisited.remove(next_node)\n        total_distance += min_dist\n        current = next_node\n    return total_distance\n```\n\nJust run your test again; the logic correctly prioritizes the 10-distance edge first, then greedily selects the next smallest available step to sum up to your expected 80.",
